er sick dog than her newborn son; a man watches his dream of becoming a #hero burn with the city around him; a teacher befriends a gargoyle; a coalition of women fighting for bodily autonomy turn to the ultimate shock-performance protest. Taking on the social collective, the performance of death, the political battleground, and the search for existential happiness with fearlessness and verve, Not the Apocalypse I Was Hoping For is full of sharp observation, irreverence, wit, and compassion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aShort stories, Canadian. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aabortion.  aalberta author.  aart.  aaward winning.  acanadian author.  adeath.  afamily.  afiction.  afran kimmel.  agothic.  agrief.  alisa moore.  aliterary.  alittle bird award.  amotherhood.  amothers.  aollection.  arelationships.  asarah selecky.  asatirical.  ashaena lambert.  ashort stories.  asocial isolation.  asocial media.  asociety.  awoman author.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781773853703?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781773853703423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781773853703/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles